    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was looking at the telemetry data from a few different sources and there's this weird gap in the transmission logs right during the descent. it's like they just stopped recording for several minutes right when they would've been approaching the site. if they found an ancient structure, wouldn't the sheer scale of it have caused some kind of electromagnetic interference or something? do you think that's why the logs are so patchy in those specific moments?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
