      "content": "exactly. and if the interference was that strong, it wouldnt just be a glitch, it would be a systemic attempt to mask the signal. i feel like if we can map out exactly which specific frequencies were being disrupted during those gaps, we might be able to infer the type of energy being emitted by whatever was down there. what kind of geological or structural features would produce that kind of reading? like, what should i be looking for in the sensor data to prove it wasn't just solar flares or something mundane?",
